{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e8850579-eec4-4289-ab3c-9d8da4bd958e","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit (v2)**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit (v3)**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or conditionally:\n[Fact(SkipWhen = typeof(SomeCondition))]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nKey differences: xUnit sets `Skip` as a property on `[Fact]`/`[Theory]`, while MSTest and NUnit use a separate `[Ignore]` attribute, and TUnit uses `[Skip]`. All accept a reason string.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"953b5a26-91b9-4c08-8492-d6b9bac76464","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax for skipping tests with a reason message in MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":292,"requestId":"4808:1F56EA:77F92C:8A62B6:69FBE745"},"id":"a5cb6602-e309-402f-9a47-37cf5b00aa63","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:13:47.426Z","parentId":"92c4b2d1-ae22-4176-a08c-6ef7333ddfe5"}
